data.comment: Today's referee, Andreas Ekberg, has blown to start the match.
Throw-in for Hammarby in their own half.
In the minute 4, Aron Johannsson puts the ball in the net and the away team now lead 0-1.
Great play from Vladimir Rodic to set up the goal.
Djurgarden are pushing forward but Emmanuel Banda's finish is wide of the goal.
In the minute 7, Goal kick for Hammarby at Tele2 Arena.
Ball safe as Hammarby is awarded a throw-in in their half.
Elliot Kack (Djurgarden) gets in a strike but the shot is blocked by a defender.
In the minute 8, Djurgarden awarded a free kick in their own half.
Andreas Ekberg signals a throw-in for Djurgarden, close to Hammarby's area.
Free kick for Hammarby in their own half.
In the minute 12, Jesper Karlstrom of Djurgarden gets in a strike, but is off target.
Ball goes out of play for a Hammarby goal kick.
Andreas Ekberg awards the home team a throw-in.
In the minute 14, Gustav Ludwigson for the away team is judged to be offside.
Andreas Ekberg signals a free kick to Hammarby in their own half.
Hammarby's Vladimir Rodic is on target but unsuccessful.
In the minute 17, Corner awarded to Hammarby.
Mads Fenger (Hammarby) is first to the ball but his header is off-target.
Andreas Ekberg awards Djurgarden a goal kick.
In the minute 17, Can Hammarby get the ball into an attacking position from this throw-in in Djurgarden's half?
Gustav Ludwigson of Hammarby smashes in a shot on target. The keeper saves, though.
In the minute 21, Hammarby have been awarded a corner by Andreas Ekberg.
The away team have replaced Aron Johannsson with Imad Khalili. This is the first substitution made today by Stefan Billborn.
Hammarby awarded a throw-in in their own half.
Andreas Ekberg signals a free kick to Hammarby in their own half.
In the minute 23, Throw-in for Djurgarden at Tele2 Arena.
Hammarby drives forward and Gustav Ludwigson gets in a shot. Without netting, however.
Djurgarden awarded a free kick in their own half.
In the minute 25, Andreas Ekberg signals a Djurgarden throw-in in Hammarby's half.
A throw-in for the home team on the opposite half.
Throw-in for Djurgarden in the half of Hammarby.
In the minute 26, It's getting dangerous! Free kick for Djurgarden close to the penalty box.
Djurgarden pushes forward through Aslak Witry, whose finish on goal is saved.
Free kick for Djurgarden in their own half.
In the minute 28, Throw-in for Djurgarden close to the penalty box.
Djurgarden to take a throw-in in Hammarby territory.
Corner awarded to Djurgarden.
In the minute 31, Djurgarden surge into the attack at Tele2 Arena but Kalle Holmberg’s header is off-target.
Hammarby have a goal kick.
Throw-in Djurgarden.
In the minute 33, Goal! Hammarby extend their lead to 0-2 through Imad Khalili.
That's a fine assist from Gustav Ludwigson.
Hammarby to take a throw-in in Djurgarden territory.
In the minute 36, Andreas Ekberg signals a free kick to Hammarby.
Imad Khalili of Hammarby is pulled up for offside.
Andreas Ekberg signals a free kick to Djurgarden in their own half.
In the minute 37, Djurgarden awarded a free kick in their own half.
Free kick for Djurgarden in their own half.
In the minute 39, In Stockholm a free kick has been awarded the home team.
David Fallman is booked for the away team.
Djurgarden attack but Jonathan Augustinsson's header doesn't find the target.
It's a goal kick for the away team in Stockholm.
In the minute 41, Djurgarden's Jonathan Augustinsson is whistled for offside at Tele2 Arena.
Andreas Ekberg will wait an extra 1 minutes before blowing the whistle to end the 1st half.
A throw-in for the away team on the opposite half.
In the minute 45, The first-half has ended.
The second-half is underway in Stockholm.
Free kick for Hammarby in the half of Djurgarden.
In the minute 47, Free kick Hammarby.
Hammarby awarded a free kick in their own half.
Throw-in high up the field for Hammarby in Stockholm.
In the minute 53, Can Djurgarden capitalize from this throw-in deep inside Hammarby's half?
It's a goal kick for the away team in Stockholm.
Free kick for Hammarby in the half of Djurgarden.
In the minute 56, Hammarby needs to be cautious. Djurgarden have an attacking throw-in.
Djurgarden's Jonathan Augustinsson has run offside.
Throw-in for Djurgarden at Tele2 Arena.
In the minute 58, Hammarby awarded a throw-in in their own half.
In Stockholm a free kick has been awarded the home team.
Kalle Bjorklund (Hammarby) gets a yellow card.
In the minute 60, Throw-in Djurgarden.
Djurgarden are coming forward and Jonathan Augustinsson gets in a strike, it misses the target, however.
Hammarby have a goal kick.
In the minute 63, Free kick Djurgarden.
The away team replace Darijan Bojanic with Serge Martinsson Ngouali.
Fredrik Ulvestad's header is off-target for Djurgarden.
Ball goes out of play for a Hammarby goal kick.
Kevin Walker is on a sub for Jonathan Ring for Djurgarden.
In the minute 64, Djurgarden make their second substitution with Emir Kujovic replacing Emmanuel Banda.
In the minute 66, Andreas Ekberg signals a free kick to Djurgarden in their own half.
Free kick for Hammarby in their own half.
Ball safe as Djurgarden is awarded a throw-in in their half.
In the minute 67, Andreas Ekberg signals a free kick to Djurgarden in their own half.
Gustav Ludwigson (Hammarby) has been booked and must now be careful not to get a second yellow card.
Jeppe Andersen (Hammarby) gets booked by Andreas Ekberg, and will miss the next match due to the number of yellow cards received this season.
In the minute 68, Djurgarden's Jesper Karlstrom has been booked in Stockholm and will miss the next match through suspension.
Throw-in for Hammarby in their own half.
Goal kick for Hammarby at Tele2 Arena.
In the minute 71, Djurgarden drive forward but Emir Kujovic is judged offside.
Hammarby pushes forward through Imad Khalili, whose finish on goal is saved.
Djurgarden have been awarded a corner by Andreas Ekberg.
In the minute 74, Mads Fenger scores an unfortunate own goal. This makes it 1-2 at Tele2 Arena.
Hammarby have been awarded a corner by Andreas Ekberg.
Andreas Ekberg awards the home team a throw-in.
In the minute 77, Free kick for Hammarby in their own half.
Hammarby's Abdul Khalili gets his shot away but it misses the target.
Andreas Ekberg awards Djurgarden a goal kick.
In the minute 79, Ball safe as Hammarby is awarded a throw-in in their half.
Andreas Ekberg blows against Djurgarden's Jonathan Augustinsson for offside.
Djurgarden awarded a free kick in their own half.
In the minute 81, Kevin Walker for Djurgarden is whistled offside.
Andreas Ekberg signals a Hammarby throw-in in Djurgarden's half.
Hammarby have a dangerous throw-in.
In the minute 83, Djurgarden awarded a free kick in their own half.
Stefan Billborn is making the team's third substitution at Tele2 Arena with Aimar Sher replacing Abdul Khalili.
Throw-in for Djurgarden in the half of Hammarby.
In the minute 84, Throw-in for Hammarby in their own half.
Andreas Ekberg waits before resuming play because Jonathan Augustinsson for Djurgarden is still down.
Djurgarden’s Jonathan Augustinsson is on his feet again at Tele2 Arena.
In the minute 86, In Stockholm, Jeppe Andersen of Hammarby is presented with a shooting opportunity. But the strike is blocked by the covering defence.
Can Hammarby capitalize from this throw-in deep inside Djurgarden's half?
Ball goes out of play for a Djurgarden goal kick.
In the minute 87, Andreas Ekberg signals a free kick to Djurgarden.
The home team has substituted Jonathan Augustinsson with Jesper Nyholm. Thomas Lagerlof is thus making his third change.
Corner awarded to Djurgarden.
In the minute 89, Corner awarded to Djurgarden.
Andreas Ekberg signals a free kick to Hammarby in their own half.
In Stockholm a free kick has been awarded the away team.
Andreas Ekberg signals a throw-in for Hammarby, close to Djurgarden's area.
The 2nd half is prolonged by 4 minutes of added time.
Djurgarden needs to be cautious. Hammarby have an attacking throw-in.
Free kick for Djurgarden in their own half.
Djurgarden's Kalle Holmberg breaks free at Tele2 Arena. But the strike goes wide of the post.
Hammarby have a goal kick.
Free kick for Hammarby in their own half.
Djurgarden awarded a throw-in in their own half.
Andreas Ekberg signals a free kick to Hammarby in their own half.
Andreas Ekberg signals a free kick to Hammarby.
Full-time! The final score is 1-2.
Aimar Sher (Hammarby) has been given a yellow card and will be suspended from the next match.
